The course deals with both classical and modern biotechnology, including the principles of gene manipulation in prokaryotic and eukaryotic organisms and applications of recombinant DNA technology in microbial and eukaryotic systems in different areas from agriculture and industry to medicine.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of molecular biotechnology lecture course is to introduce methods of modern biotechnology and their application in science, technology and everyday lifeLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected: To be familiar with the position of biotechnology in today's world To acquire the knowledge about main research methods in today's molecular biology and gene technology (enzymatic and chemical synthesis of DNA, DNA cloning, hybridization techniques, PCR, sequencing, directed mutagenesis and mutation analysis). To be familiar with latest developments in the field of DNA and RNA research methods. To be able to see relationships between different technologies and research methods To have overview about applications of classical biotechnology in industry, agriculture, environmental protection and medicine To have overview about applications of molecular biotechnology in industry, agriculture, environmental protection and medicine
